body:
# Stripe Checkout

Checkout provides a Stripe-hosted payment page that handles the entire payment UI, including card input, validation, SCA/3DS authentication, and localization. Create a session server-side, redirect the customer to the hosted page, and handle the result. You will need a `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` from your [[stripe]] dashboard.

## Create a Checkout Session

### One-Time Payment

```javascript
import Stripe from 'stripe';
const stripe = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY);

const session = await stripe.checkout.sessions.create({
  mode: 'payment',
  line_items: [
    {
      price_data: {
        currency: 'usd',
        product_data: { name: 'T-Shirt' },
        unit_amount: 2000,  // $20.00
      },
      quantity: 1,
    },
  ],
  success_url: 'https://example.com/success?session_id={CHECKOUT_SESSION_ID}',
  cancel_url: 'https://example.com/cancel',
});

console.log(session.id);   // cs_xxx
console.log(session.url);  // https://checkout.stripe.com/c/pay/cs_xxx
// Redirect customer to session.url
```

### Subscription

```javascript
const session = await stripe.checkout.sessions.create({
  mode: 'subscription',
  line_items: [
    { price: 'price_xxx', quantity: 1 },  // Existing recurring price
  ],
  success_url: 'https://example.com/success?session_id={CHECKOUT_SESSION_ID}',
  cancel_url: 'https://example.com/cancel',
});
// Creates a customer and subscription automatically
```

See [[stripe/subscriptions#prices-products]] for setting up recurring prices.

## Line Items

Line items define what the customer is buying:

```javascript
// Using an existing price
{ price: 'price_xxx', quantity: 2 }

// Using ad-hoc price data
{
  price_data: {
    currency: 'usd',
    product_data: {
      name: 'Custom Item',
      description: 'A detailed description',
      images: ['https://example.com/image.png'],
    },
    unit_amount: 1500,  // $15.00
  },
  quantity: 1,
}

// Adjustable quantity
{
  price: 'price_xxx',
  quantity: 1,
  adjustable_quantity: { enabled: true, minimum: 1, maximum: 10 },
}
```

## Custom Fields

Collect additional information during checkout:

```javascript
const session = await stripe.checkout.sessions.create({
  mode: 'payment',
  line_items: [{ price: 'price_xxx', quantity: 1 }],
  custom_fields: [
    {
      key: 'engraving',
      label: { type: 'custom', custom: 'Engraving text' },
      type: 'text',
      optional: false,
    },
  ],
  success_url: 'https://example.com/success',
  cancel_url: 'https://example.com/cancel',
});
```

## Fulfillment

After payment, fulfill the order using one of two approaches:

1. **Success URL** — retrieve the session on your success page:

```javascript
const session = await stripe.checkout.sessions.retrieve(sessionId, {
  expand: ['line_items'],
});
if (session.payment_status === 'paid') {
  // Fulfill the order
}
```

2. **Webhooks** (recommended) — listen for `checkout.session.completed`:

See [[stripe/webhooks]] for setting up webhook handlers. The webhook approach is more reliable because customers may close the browser before reaching the success URL.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Server-side API key (`sk_test_...` or `sk_live_...`) |
